(1) A person shall not intentionally and without lawful authority, interfere with data or a computer system of another person in a way which— (a) causes the data or computer system to be modified, destroyed, altered or otherwise rendered ineffective; (b) obstructs, interrupts or interferes with another person’s lawful use of data; (c) denies access to data to a person who is authorised to access it; (d) causes data of another person to deteriorate; or (e) deletes data of another person.
