(1) A person commits an offence if that person intentionally— (a) produces child pornography for the purpose of its distribution through a computer or computer system ; (b) sells, imports, exports or makes available any pornography to a child through a computer or computer system ; (c) compels, invites or allows a child to view pornography through a computer or computer system ; (d) offers or makes available child pornography through a computer or computer system ; (e) distributes or transmits child pornography through a computer or computer system ; (f) procures and obtains child pornography through a computer or computer system for oneself or for another person; (g) possesses child pornography in a computer or computer system or on a computer data storage medium ; or (h) obtains access of child pornography through a computer or computer system .
