(1) A person shall not intentionally and without lawful authority— (a) use a computer or computer system to relay or retransmit electronic communications to deceive or mislead users of a computer or computer system as to the origin of such communication ; (b) initiate the transmission of multiple electronic messages from or through a computer or computer system for purposes of causing harm or disrupting the computer or computer system ; (c) establish a software application system with the intent to deceive or mislead a visitor to the software application system as to the authenticity of the software application system for the purpose of gaining unauthorised access to information to commit an offence; or (d) falsify header information in an electronic communication and initiate the transmission of such electronic communication to commit an offence, deceive or mislead users.
